When using the new class-field syntax for methods in a React class component, do you use it for the methods that already have access to the instance as well?

render = () => (
  <div>...</div>
);

I like the idea of not having to type the return keyword.

Thoughts?

Just remember that using this

render = () => (
<div>...</div>
);

Will mofe the render method into the constructor of your class so hot reloading will not work. Other than that it is extremely useful. You don't have to bind methods anymore. You don't have to create new function handlers in onClick properties because you can just create a factory: () => () => ({})

const Number = ({ number }) => {
  if (!number) return <div>don't have a number</div>

  return <div>the number is {number}</div>
}

